{
  "text": "The data was analyzed by means of linear mixed-effects models. The data of Part I did not reveal that stimuli length affects annoyance (p:0.52). Similar results were found by [CITATION_1] for lengths of 1-30min. The data of Part 2 showed a quadratic dependence of the perceived length on the real stimulus length (Fig. 1) , which was confirmed by the linear mixed effects model (p :0.03). Further, the optimal length (spot-on) was found to be 20 s (Fig. I ) .",
